Lizeka TandwaParamedics at the scene where children inhaled toxic fumes. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories The scene of an accident which claimed two lives and left 64 others injured in Parkview, north of Johannesburg, on Friday was "terrible and horrific", an eyewitness told News24.WATCHJohannesburg &ndash; 31 school children were rushed to hospital after breathing in possible toxic fumes at the Zoo Lake public swimming pool when hydrochloric acid was apparently poured into it on Saturday.Emer-G-Med spokesperson Max Cohen said its paramedics responded to the call earlier on Saturday."A total of 31 school children between the ages of 2 years and 12 years sustained inhalation injuries ranging from minor to moderate."Cohen said the children were treated at the scene before being taken to a hospital nearby.He said it was alleged that hydrochloric acid was poured into the pool that they were swimming in. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.